==Portrayal in adaptations==
[[File:The Lord of the Rings Online - Armor of Castamir.jpg|thumb|150px|The armor of the Usurper in ''[[The Lord of the Rings Online]]'']]
'''2015: ''[[The Lord of the Rings Online]]'':'''
:Castamir's armor is recovered from the [[Crossings of Erui]] and is taken to [[Pelargir]] for safekeeping. Castamir's legacy never fully went away, as non-negligible number of Gondorians remained secret supporters of his through generations, plotting against Steward [[Denethor]] and later King [[Aragorn|Elessar]].

:During the [[War of the Ring]], the [[Corsairs of Umbar]] besieging [[Gondor]] were led by four brothers calling themselves "the Heirs of Castamir", though their claim was ultimately proven to be false. Though all of them perished during the fighting, the eldest left an adult son in Umbar, who continued posing a threat to [[Gondor]].

